summary: The provided texts regulate different aspects of real estate finance. The primary document (EBA GL 2020/06) specifies detailed informational and documentary requirements for credit institutions during the loan origination process for specific types of real estate lending. The related documents cover different regulatory subjects, such as definitions for capital adequacy purposes (Basel Framework, CRR), collateral eligibility and valuation for credit risk mitigation (CRR, Basel Framework), management of non-performing exposures, supervisory review processes (SREP), and rules for authorities setting risk weights. Because the documents apply to different actors, regulatory actions, or functional contexts, no true overlaps or contradictions were found under the strict definitions provided.
